  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Gopal Singh & Anr. versus State of Uttarakhand pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_2_1174_1177','2025INSC263'); ><font size='4'> <strong>GOPAL SINGH & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF UTTARAKHAND </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 2 S.C.R. 1174</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 263</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010003032025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Trial court convicted the appellants under Sections 302 and 323 read with Section 34 of the Indian Penal Code, 1860. High Court altered the conviction to Section 304 Part II, IPC. Whether the identity of the appellants as accused was established. Appellants, if entitled Identity as accused not established &ndash; Trial court convicted the appellants u/ss.302, 323 r/w s.34, IPC &ndash; High Court altered the conviction to s.304 Part II, IPC &ndash; Interference with: Held: Identity of the present appellants as accused was not established before the Court by any<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 06-02-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 1408/2014</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_2_1174_1177','2025INSC263','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'>